STUDENT RADIO AT VCU

2022 NFL Mock Draft by Yanni Kouiroukidis

By Yanni Kouiroukidis

It’s time to lock in. I am three weeks away from graduating college, which is insane to think about. However, the time is now. A time that is greatly appreciated by football fans all over the country. It is NFL Draft season. The prospects are off the charts this year at positions like edge rusher, wide receiver and cornerback. With the madness that this off-season has created only time will tell to see who will come out of this draft victorious. Last year I did a full seven-round mock draft. I predicted all 259 picks in the draft. For time sake I don’t know if I’ll do that again. I guess it will just depend on how the first round goes. Without further ado, let’s start the official YSN 2022 NFL Mock Draft.

LISTEN TO WVCW ON THE GO

Support wvcw

College radio is one of the last outlets for creative radio programming and a training ground for the future of the industry.

With your help we can keep the students on the air for years to come.

STUDIO SPOTLIGHT

March Madness is Coming

Join the WVCW Sports Team as they count you down to March Madness! It kicks off with the A-10 tournament in Washington DC 3/9-3/13!

WVCW ON RADIOFX

Download the RadioFX app for the best college radio experience anywhere.

Interact with DJs and other listeners, Participate in polls & contests, View programming scheduled to discover the music and content that interests you, And much more!

ALUMNI: WE WANT TO HEAR FROM YOU!

Bored? Feeling trapped inside? Longing for an outlet? Return to your roots and do a radio show! The WVCW Alumni Show is your opportunity to return to the airwaves!

CHALKBOARD Sessions

Our award winning Chalkboard Sessions invite artists into our office to play in front of our chalkboard wall. The shows are first posted on Facebook, but will appear here on the website as well.
